reviews.review_text: i needed swuash for a ratatouille this week. i ordered two plus zucchini. they are only about 3" long and a bit softened. $.89/each is ridiculous!!!

reviews.title: If you order 5, you will get 4 good ones.
reviews.review_text: They always give you one very bad item if you order multiple of the same item. Why is that? They must be trained to do this as it happens every time.

reviews.title: Produce goes bad in 2 days
reviews.review_text: Do not buy fresh produce from Walmart their food goes bad in two days. All my fruits and veggies are money wasted.

reviews.title: Simple directions ignored
reviews.review_text: I ordered 4 squash to make a small casserole and received ONE. So now I have to go back to the store

reviews.title: Choose better fresh vegetables.
reviews.review_text: The yellow squash was too large, seedy and tough skin. Workers should be trained on how to choose better fresh vegetables.

reviews.title: Yellow Yummy Squash
reviews.review_text: So many delicious dishes to make with this yellow squash. Still learning how to cook with it. Squash casserole was a HIT!

reviews.title: Don't let them pick vegetables
reviews.review_text: Don't order produce for pickup or delivery. Constantly adjust quantities without notice or send rotten fruits and vegetables that are unusable.

reviews.title: Does this look like 12 squash that I paid for?
reviews.review_text: I asked for 12 Squash‚Ä¶.12!!! When I opened the bag, there are only 5 in here! Stuff like this keeps happening over and over! and you guys definitely charged me for 12‚Ä¶.not 5!!!

reviews.title: Not buying fresh produce at Walmart again.
reviews.review_text: We bought 2- yellow squash. One was for tonight's dinner, one for another night. I was putting the groceries away and while taking the squash out of the bag, my finger went right thru one of them. What happened to the people that used to pick good produce?

reviews.title: Order not complete and I was not told of it.
reviews.review_text: I ordered 3 yellow squash, but only received 1 of them. Both the app and the person loading my car declared that my order was complete. But it clearly wasn't. So now I have to drive back into town to get more yellow squash and go inide the store to buy it, which I was trying to avoid, because of COVID! Your store does not enforce the Illinois mask mandate, so going inside the store is dangerous to my health.! I hate having to endanger myself because you did not fulfill my entire order AND didn't even inform me that you hadn't!!!

reviews.title: Perfect baked, makes a great side dish
reviews.review_text: As always the squash came perfect and ready to bake. The Walmart shopper did a great job at picking out the best one! Our favorite way to enjoy this squash is to cut it up into thick slices and drizzle olive oil on it, toss a pinch of salt and pepper over it and bake it in the oven at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes. It comes out perfect every time and it's enjoyable with most every meal as the vegetable side.

reviews.title: Nasty, nasty, nasty
reviews.review_text: It seems to me that the associates that do the shopping have been trained to grab the oldest yuckiest looking produce when you use the pick up service. These were so beat up and bruised. They had sunk in areas and just nasty looking. I threw them right in the trash.

reviews.title: Amount requested not followed
reviews.review_text: I ordered this item as a substitution for zucchini if that was not available. I ordered "1" and received 5. A bit excessive. I wonder if I am ordering incorrectly. When I request "1" of a vegetable, is it assumed that I am ordering 1 lb.? This is the second time I've received multiple units when I ordered "1". I don't want to repeat this mistake again. Am I doing something incorrect when placing the order?

I really needed zucchini. I did not think you would give me a different vegetable as a substitute. I thought it would be an organic option or something of the same vegetable ordered. This was very frustrating that I had to drive up to the store to buy it separately. Why didn't you just give me what the zucchini that was at the store?

reviews.title: Pitiful produce
reviews.review_text: Rotten squash. I paid extra to have it delivered but in order to get any credit back for it I have to drive to the store and take it back......pitiful service. Who are you using to pick out the produce........has this person ever cooked in their lives>

reviews.title: WaytogoWalmart
reviews.review_text: Ordered zucchini Walmart substituted out, yellow crookneck squash (alright with me I like both). For the yellow crookneck i was charged $.94 per lbs. for the substituted zucchini with yellow crookneck squash i was charged $1.62 per lbs. Way to go Walmart. I'll not except substituted items any longer.

reviews.title: rotten veggies and cracked eggs
reviews.review_text: all veggies from this order were rotten or damaged! one dozen eggs from order before were cracked only could salvage a few. thats why i ordered so many this time. trying to get what i needed. i guess ill have to get onions, squash. zuccini, potatoes elsewhere!

reviews.title: Sad squash
reviews.review_text: I love Walmart pick-up‚Ä¶ and it's just $1.10 for two yellow squash‚Ä¶ one was all jacked up with cuts and bruises and the other was so soft you could bend it‚Ä¶ I was planning to make soup ‚Ä¶ instead tossed into the trash‚Ä¶ whoever picked that squash didn't care‚Ä¶ maybe they were over the day‚Ä¶ it was squishy, discolored and almost flat‚Ä¶ like for real? I'm so disappointed. There's a difference between not really knowing and not really caring‚Ä¶

reviews.title: I would have never chosen rotten squash!
reviews.review_text: I guess I won't be able to have produce delivered anymore because it looks like they pick out the worst, possible looking produce they can find to get rid of it! This squash was half ruined, old, dried up. I had to cut half of it off to salvage a couple of servings. Really, aren't we paying enough? I would have never bought this unless I was picking it out with my eyes shut!

reviews.title: Not a good day for me.
reviews.review_text: I ordered yellow squash BUT I received zucchini. So, I didn't get what I needed for a recipe AND I was charged more for yellow squash. I also received a damaged can of paint that I didn't order. It's an obvious return from someone else. Am I a paint recycling service? I'm not paying to dispose of Walmarts paint.

reviews.title: Very dissatisfied üòü
reviews.review_text: Yellow squash was extremely small! Really not big enough to use. Ridiculous choice to send home with customer!!! Had to go to Publix and get squash before I could prepare dinner. Not worth trouble to ask for refund because $.08 was amount charged. That indicates how small squash was.

reviews.title: Gourds for dinner? I invited Jack of ‚ÄúBeanstock‚Äù
reviews.review_text: The only problem I had with this order was the size of the squash and zucchini. They were each about 12inches long and 3-4 inches in circumference. Needless to say, they are not good to eat having reached the hardness of a gourd and so can't be cooked to a point of tenderness.

reviews.title: Not fit for human consumption
reviews.review_text: Unreal. The squash I received were old, brown spots and puckered. Who eats that? By the time they reach that stage they're bitter and nasty. What's the matter with the shoppers? I don't blame them as much as their managers. The shoppers at my store are young people who most likely have never boiled an egg. It's a training issue plain and simple! Look at the picture. The one on the right is what all three should look like.

I bought three squash they had to adjust the weight to an extra dollar because all three were so big and firm I don't know why everybody else got such small ones maybe you're not a good customer like me but I would like to say the driver must not be too smart because she set my food in front of the door I'm disabled got rid of my Walker got two door door would not push open because all the food was sitting right in front of it I was able to push it open far enough to try to get it back without tearing up everything don't have any idea what was on her mind but it was not delivering groceries but squash was good

reviews.title: did not get these
reviews.review_text: I ordered 3 squash and I got 3 lovely squash but you charge me for 6. The 3 I got were all small so I'm assuming that what I got were the least expensive so you owe me $1.43. I've had something like this happen before but I did not report. I would have just kept them and said nothing but you charged me for them and I DID NOT GET THEM. Please refund my account. Everything else was great as usual. Thank You Still a loyal customer.

reviews.title: Online shoppers are being jipped
reviews.review_text: Why was this even picked as a squash? Once you get past the rind there is no squash. And I keep getting extremely small vegetables when I order from the produce section here recently. It's getting to be absolutely ridiculous and it's not worth the money. If I'm paying $10 for delivery why do I keep ending up with the worst possible produce... Y'all recently did this with my litter today. I will be going into the store tomorrow even though I'm without a car. I do anticipate walking to the store to see if my litter was available. I will also be stopping by the produce section to see what all options were available before this became my only possible choice of squash.

reviews.title: Sad produce! Spoiled %26 old produce=why?
reviews.review_text: Whoever picks the fresh produce has surely never cooked! Second time this week produce a disappointment. Two squash (.23 cents!) were wrinkled, limp as a wet rag, %26 had brown spots. So small, not worth using. Maybe the crows will eat them. Am home bound, depend on delivery; can't depend on getting fresh produce. They want to get rid of old stuff fast! DO NOT want refund or exchange BUT PLEASE instruct "pickers" on what not to choose. Thank you.
Had 7 on my grocery list, ONLY RECEIVED 2 YELLOW SQUASH.
